properties.areaDesc: Eastern Sierra Slopes of Inyo County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 2:02PM PST until January 17 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Las Vegas NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Total accumulations of 5 to 10 inches above 6000
feet, with 1-3 inches above 5000 feet. Winds gusting as high as
45 mph near exposed ridgelines.

* WHERE...Eastern Sierra Slopes.

* WHEN...From 10 AM Thursday to 4 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches. The cold wind chills as low as 20
below zero could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little
as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow means periods of snow will
cause primarily travel difficulties. Expect snow covered roads
and limited visibilities, and use caution while driving.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THURSDAY TO 4 AM PST FRIDAY for the Eastern Sierra Slopes
